Description: Provides reusable functions for loading, processing, and
    visualizing energy consumption data produced by population-based
    metaheuristics measured via Intel/AMD RAPL (Running Average Power Limit)
    counters, as accessed through tools such as 'pinpoint'. Typical workflows
    include computing energy deltas relative to a baseline, summarizing results
    across algorithmic parameter combinations, running Wilcoxon rank-sum
    statistical tests, and producing publication-quality 'ggplot2' visualizations.
    The package was originally developed to support the research papers of the
    Brave New Green Algorithm project
    (<https://github.com/JJ/brave-new-green-algorithm>), including
    Merelo and Merelo Molina (2026) <https://ojs.ub.uni-konstanz.de/formosus/index.php/ola/article/view/48>,
    Merelo-Guervos et al. (2025) <doi:10.1007/978-3-031-90065-5_15>, and
    Merelo-Guervos et al. (2025) "Time-related effects in the measurement of
    energy consumption in evolutionary algorithms".
